### 3. Google OAuth Login

**Backend:** [api/google-login.php](file:///c:/xampp2/htdocs/uplodedFile/api/google-login.php)
- Verifies Google ID tokens
- Extracts user information (email, name, Google ID)
- Creates National ID format: `GOOGLE-{first10digits}`
- Creates new user or logs in existing user
- Stores data in `users` and `user_profiles` tables

**Frontend:**
- Google Sign-In SDK loaded
- Click Google button ‚Üí OAuth popup
- Token sent to PHP backend
- Success overlay shows "Welcome! Logging you in via Google..."
- Redirects to dashboard

### 4. Facebook OAuth Login

**Backend:** [api/facebook-login.php](file:///c:/xampp2/htdocs/uplodedFile/api/facebook-login.php)
- Verifies Facebook access tokens
- Calls Facebook Graph API for user data
- Creates National ID format: `FB-{first10digits}`
- Creates new user or logs in existing user
- Stores data in database

**Frontend:**
- Facebook SDK loaded
- Click Facebook button ‚Üí Facebook login dialog
- Access token sent to PHP backend
- Success overlay shows "Welcome! Logging you in via Facebook..."
- Redirects to dashboard

